<div id="review_4439996746" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4439996746" />
    <a title="Kalliope" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3593962-kalliope"><img alt="Kalliope" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1428482885p2/3593962.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4439996746?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kalliope" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kalliope" href="/user/show/3593962-kalliope">Kalliope</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3593962-kalliope?shelf=2022">2022</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3593962-kalliope?shelf=fiction-italian">fiction-italian</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3593962-kalliope?shelf=re-reads">re-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3593962-kalliope?shelf=italy">italy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3593962-kalliope?shelf=20-century">20-century</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4439996746" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5317675654332871440"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1642933635i/32480812._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I arrived at this book through an exercise in my Italian textbook. The exercise was on the <i>Periodi ipotetici</i> (verb tenses used in sentences that begin with “If…..”) and the text was an interview to the director of the film “The Legend of the Pianist on the Ocean”, based on Baricco’s book. As I had read <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/91887.Seta' title='Seta by Alessandro Baricco' rel='nofollow noopener'>Seta</a>, I knew that Baricco’s language was manageable.<br/><br/>The novel is really a play to be performed by just one character on the stage at a time. It is not really a monologue as the subtitle indicates,</span>
  <span id="freeText5317675654332871440" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1642933635i/32480812._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I arrived at this book through an exercise in my Italian textbook. The exercise was on the <i>Periodi ipotetici</i> (verb tenses used in sentences that begin with “If…..”) and the text was an interview to the director of the film “The Legend of the Pianist on the Ocean”, based on Baricco’s book. As I had read <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/91887.Seta" title="Seta by Alessandro Baricco" rel="nofollow noopener">Seta</a>, I knew that Baricco’s language was manageable.<br><br>The novel is really a play to be performed by just one character on the stage at a time. It is not really a monologue as the subtitle indicates, as two characters, a pianist and a trumpetist speak out. It can be read easily as a novel, and therefore lies, as Baricco says, <i>in bilico</i> or in between the prose and drama genres. <br><br>It reads like a fairy tale of sweet impossibles. Initially set in the interwar period it presents the life of an orphan abandoned in a ship, the <i>Virginian</i>, by immigrants to the US. The orphan, Danny Boodmann TD Lemon Novecento, Novecento in short, becomes a pianist of skilful hands who does not want to leave the boat for the rest of his life. <br><br>The tale has a magic plot and raises, candidly, simple and complex questions on life, happiness, and perception. There is humour, there are allegorical suggestions, there is pessimism and there is joy. One of the sweetest scenes is the account of a grand piano, loosened from its fasting to the floor of the ship, dancing maddeningly from one side of the dance hall to the other, lolled by the waves of a nasty storm, with the abstracted pianist having the time of his life.<br><br>Below is the link to the film in YT.<br><br><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R0u8S5nMwZo">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R0u8S...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="5317675654332871440" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


