      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/908.Alessandro_Baricco">About Alessandro Baricco</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/908.Alessandro_Baricco"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1406652399p3/908.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/908.Alessandro_Baricco">Alessandro Baricco
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
2,993
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5250800334404264784">Alessandro Baricco is a popular Italian writer, director, and performer. His novels have been translated into a wide number of languages, and include Lands of Glass, Silk, Ocean Sea, City, and Without Blood. His theatrical monologue, Novecento, was adapted into film, titled The Legend of 1900.<br/>He currently lives in Rome with his wife and two sons.</span>

</div>
</div>

